sentences: Dax David Riggs (born October 15, 1973) is an American musician, best known for fronting the sludge metal band Acid Bath in the 1990s.
Dax David Riggs (born October 15, 1973) is an American musician, best known for fronting the sludge metal band Acid Bath in the 1990s.
In 2007 he began releasing material under his own name.
The band released one demo, Wet Dreams of the Insane (1991), under that name before changing it.
Daisyhead & The Mooncrickets was a project of Riggs between 1995 and 1997 that never took off.

Only two Daisyhead recordings are known to exist: Skeletal Circus Derails, a six-song recording from 1995, and a self-titled 14-track album from 1997, where most of the songs are cut off before they end.
